                                      29 *        SYSUT4  LISTING A-TEXT FROM PHASE 1                            00290021
                                      30 *                DATA A-TEXT FROM PHASE 2                               00300021

                                      32 *                E-TEXT FROM ALL PHASES                                 00320021

                                      34 *OUTPUT:                                                                00340021
                                      35 *                                                                       00350021
                                      36 *        SYSPRINT - PROCEDURE LIST                                      00360021
                                      37 *        SYSLIN - OBJECT MODULE FOR LIKAGE EDITOR                       00370021
                                      38 *        SYSPUNCH - OUTPUT DECK                                         00380021
                                      39 *        SYSUT3  XREF REF-TEXT, ETEXT                                   00390021
                                      40 *        SYSUT1  XREF DEF-TEXT                                          00400021
                                      41 *                                                                       00410021
                                      42 *FUNCTION/OPERATION:                                                    00420021
                                      43 *                                                                       00430021
                                      44 *   PHASE 6 COMBINES ALL THE INFORMATION IN THE PROCEDURE A TEXT, D     00440021
                                      45 *   A-TEXT, AND OPTIMAZATION A-TEXT TO PRODUCE OBJECT MODULE SUITAB     00450021
                                      46 *   FOR INPUT TO LINKAGE EDITOR, AND PRODUCES PUNCHED OBJECT DECK       00460021
                                      47 *   AND AN OBJECT MODULE LISTING IF THEY ARE REQUESTED BY THE USER.     00470021
                                      48 *                                                                       00480021
                                      49 *EXTERNAL ROUTINES:                                                     00490021
                                      50 *                                                                       00500021
                                      51 *        PHASE 00 - LINK TO I-O AND INTERPHASE REGION                   00510021
                                      52 *        TAMEIN - TAMER INITIALIZATION                                  00520021
                                      53 *        PRIME  - ALLOCATE SPACE IN TABLE REGION                        00530021
                                      54 *        INSERT - OBTAIN ROOM FOR AN ENTRY TO BE MADE IN A TABLE        00540021
                                      55 *        STATIC - NOTES NO NEW ENTRY TO BE MADE. RELEASE UNUSED TAB     00550021

                                    3630 *=1                                ADR ELEMENT                          34160021
                                    3631 *      FORMAT  //78 IDDD KK TTTTTT //                                   34170021
                                    3632 *              WHERE I=0   BL-I                                         34180021
                                    3633 *                     1   BLL                                           34190021
                                    3634 *                     2   BLS                                           34200021
                                    3635 *                     4   SBL-I                                         34210021
                                    3636 *                     6   SUBSCRIPT CELL (NOT A BL TYPE)                34220021
                                    3637 *                     3   SEE NOTE                                      34230021
                                    3638 *                                                                       34240021
                                    3639 *                   KK=NO OF CELL OF ABOVE TYPE                         34250021
                                    3640 *                   DDD=DISP OF ITEM FROM ADDR IN SPECIFIED CELL        34260021
                                    3641 *                   TTTTTT=DICTIONARY PTR   BITS 0-1  UNUSED            34270021
                                    3642 *                                                2-14 DICT SEGMENT      34280021
                                    3643 *                                                15-23 DISP IN SEGM     34290021
                                    3644 *                                                                       34300021
                                    3645 *      IN GENERAL, AN ADR ELT IS USED TO REFER TO A DATA NAME. THE      34310021
                                    3646 *      TECHNIQUE IS TO LOAD A REGISTER WITH THE BASE LOCATER (OR        34320021
                                    3647 *      SUBSCRIPT CELL) SPECIFIED (AT OBJECT TIME THAT IS) AND THEN      34330021
                                    3648 *      TO REFER TO THAT DATA NAME THROUGH THE DISP GIVEN IN THE ADR     34340021
                                    3649 *      ELEMENT AND THE GENERAL REGISTER JUST LOADED.                    34350021
                                    3650 *                                                                       34360021
                                    3651 *      THE DICTIONARY POINTER IS USED AS A SYMBOLIC OPERAND IN THE      34370021
                                    3652 *      LISTING AND HAS A CORRESPONDENCE TO THE ITEM IN THE GLOSSARY     34380021
                                    3653 *                                                                       34390021
                                    3654 *      NOTE-IF I=3, THE MEANING IS THAT THE ADDRESS OF THE DATA NAM     34400021
                                    3655 *      HAS ALREADY BEEN LOADED INTO A REGISTER. IN THIS CASE THE DA     34410021
                                    3656 *      NAME IS REFERRED TO BY MEANS OF A ZERO DISP FROM THE REGISTE     34420021
                                    3657 *      SPECIFIED IN THE LOW-ORDER 4-BITS OF DDD.                        34430021
